result.execSummary:
The defendant Higinio Sandoval Rubalcava Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Higinio Sandoval Rubalcava Jr is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Higinio Sandoval Rubalcava Jr was found guilty of Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Higinio Sandoval Rubalcava Jr was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CORRECTION TO PLEA AND SENTENCING ENTRY ON 6/17/22: "Court advised defendant due to this DV conviction he may never possess firearms or ammunition." should be REMOVED from the entry, as it does not apply.

Defendant Higinio Sandoval Rubalcava in court with attorney Brett Lee Copeland.  Defendant Higinio Sandoval Rubalcava in custody.  Katie Bakunowicz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Plea and sentencing hearing held. State has filed an AMENDED information. Defense counsel acknowledges receipt, waives reading, and enters a temporary not guilty plea. Parties have reached an agreement. State places offer on the record. Defense and defendant are in agreement.

Pursuant to negotiations and on the Motion of the State, Court Ordered Count 1 DISMISSED.

AS TO AMENDED COUNTS 2 AND 3: Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Defendant further advised that if not a US citizen, deportation is possible. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Elements/Jury Instructions received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Parties prepared to proceed with sentencing. State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law. Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing.

AS TO COUNT 2: Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent, with credit for 140 days served. Huber privileges to be determined by HOC.

AS TO COUNT 3: Court sentenced the defendant to serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction, concurrent, with credit for 140 days served. Huber privileges to be determined by HOC.
Court STAYED the sentences and placed the defendant on probation for 18 MONTHS

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
- Complete a course in anger management.
- AODA assessment; comply with any treatment.
- Maintain absolute sobriety.
- Mental health evaluation; take all prescribed medications.
- No contact with victim unless approved by the court.
- No contact with firearms.
- Provide a DNA sample during the term of probation.
- Defendant to pay all non-waivable costs, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge during the period of probation. Failure to pay the costs and surcharges will result in a civil judgment. Court WAIVED all other court costs, fees, and surcharges due to inability to pay.

- Court set restitution at zero.

*Court advised defendant of appellant rights. 
*Court advised defendant due to this DV conviction he may never possess firearms or ammunition.
*Court ordered defendant to sign up for probation no later than 4:00 pm on 6/22/22.
